From: KMA OS <kma@kma-os.dev>
Date: Sun, 21 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] kma: add welcome banner at boot

Add "Welcome to KMA OS" banner printed from init/main.c during
kernel initialization. Visible on TTY and serial console.

Signed-off-by: KMA OS <kma@kma-os.dev>
---
 init/main.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/init/main.c b/init/main.c
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/init/main.c
+++ b/init/main.c
@@ -XXX,X +XXX,X @@ asmlinkage __visible void __init start_kernel(void)
 	/*
 	 * These use large boot-time allocations and should not be used
 	 * after boot.
 	 */
+
+	/* KMA OS welcome banner */
+	pr_info("\n");
+	pr_info("  ╔══════════════════════════════════════╗\n");
+	pr_info("  ║       Welcome to KMA OS             ║\n");
+	pr_info("  ║  Minimalist Linux Kernel             ║\n");
+	pr_info("  ╚══════════════════════════════════════╝\n");
+	pr_info("\n");
+
 	set_task_stack_end_magic(&init_task);
 	smp_setup_processor_id();
 	debug_objects_early_init();
--
2.43.0
